ek surnames based on the similar personal name <i>Efstathios</i>, such as <b>Efstathiadis</b> and   Efstathiou  . See also   Stacey  ."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":14,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":45,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":70,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":83,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":92,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Stace was born in 1245, in Kent, Kent, England. He had at least 1 son with Juliana. He died in May 1341, in Kent, England, at the age of 96, and was buried in Epping, Essex, England."},"et":{"1245–May 1341":"1245–mai 1341","1245–Female":"1245–Surnud","1277–1330":"1277–1330","–Female":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1245–1341":"1245–1341","1341":"1341","1330":"1330","1290":"1290","15 December 1330":"15. detsember 1330","May 1341":"mai 1341","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","21 May 1314":"21. mai 1314","1245":"1245","1277":"1277","1453":"1453","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Epping, Essex, England":"Epping, Essex, England","England":"England","Kent, England":"Kent, England","Kent, Kent, England":"Kent, Kent, England"},"fi":{"1245–May 1341":"1245–toukokuu 1341","1245–Female":"1245–Kuollut","1277–1330":"1277–1330","–Female":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1245–1341":"1245–1341","1341":"1341","1330":"1330","1290":"1290","15 December 1330":"15. joulukuuta 1330","May 1341":"toukokuu 1341","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","21 May 1314":"21. toukokuuta 1314","1245":"1245","1277":"1277","1453":"1453","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Epping, Essex, England":"Epping, Essex, England","England":"England","Kent, England":"Kent, England","Kent, Kent, England":"Kent, Kent, England"},"fr":{"1245–May 1341":"1245–mai 1341","1245–Female":"1245–Décédée","1277–1330":"1277–1330","–Female":"Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1245–1341":"1245–1341","1341":"1341","1330":"1330","1290":"1290","15 December 1330":"15 décembre 1330","May 1341":"mai 1341","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","21 May 1314":"21 mai 1314","1245":"1245","1277":"1277","1453":"1453","1328":"1328","1317":"